BASE URL FOR PRODUCTION BUILD: https://zn23g4uvg2.execute-api.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/prod

VALIDATIONS:
	Password must be 8 characters or more

To create a new recipe:
  POST /recipes
	JSON:
		name: string
		imageUrl: string
		description: string
		category: string
		ingredients: []string
		instructions: []string
		preparationTime: int
		isPublic: bool
		difficulty: string

To get all recipes:
	(this will return ONLY PUBLIC recipes)
	GET /recipes?category={category you want to filter by (OPTIONAL)}
	To get next batch:
		GET /recipes?last={last key returned}&category={category you want to filter by (OPTIONAL)}

To get all recipes by current user only INCLUDING PRIVATE recipes:
	GET /recipes/me
	to get next batch
	GET /recipes/me?last={last key}

To get all recipes by a user:
	GET /recipes?by={userid}
	to get next batch
	GET /recipes?by={userid}&last={last key}

To edit a recipe:
	PUT /recipes/{recipe_id}
	JSON:
		(only include properties to update not all of them)
		name: string
		description: string
		category: string
		ingredients: []string
		instructions: []string
		preparationTime: int
		isPublic: bool
		difficulty: string

To delete a recipe:
	DELETE /recipes/{recipe_id}

To add recipe to favorite:
	POST /favorites
	JSON:
		recipeId: string

To remove recipe from favorite:
	DELETE /favorites/{recipe_id}
	
To get all favorites recipes:
	GET /favorites
	To get next batch:
		GET /favorites?last={id of last favorite returned}

To rate a recipe:
	POST /ratings
	JSON:
		recipeId: string
		stars: int
		comment: string(optional)

To edit rating:
	post to the rating again it will override existing rating
	POST /ratings
	JSON:
		recipeId: string
		stars: int
		comment: string(optional)

To delete rating on a recipe:
	DELETE /ratings/{id of recipe}

To get all ratings on a recipe:
	GET /ratings/{id of recipe}
	To get next batch:
		GET /ratings/{id of recipe}?last={last key returned}

To get current user details:
	GET /users

To get any users details:
	GET /users/{id}

To edit user details:
	PUT /users
	JSON:
		(only include properties to update not all of them)
		dpUrl: string
		name: string
		bio: string 
		location: string

To get url to post pictures to:
	GET /upload-url?ext={the file extension of the image e.g .jpg, .png, .gif, etc}
			/upload-url?id={recipe or user id}&ext={file extension of image}

To search for a recipe:
	GET /search?recipe={search string}